-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 09:34AM EDT
-- None



June 12 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1330 GMT on Thursday:

** The French government met on Thursday to discuss the fate of cash-strapped engineering group Alstom <ALSO.PA> but gave little indication of its feelings towards a plan being hatched by Siemens <SIEGn.DE> and Mitsubishi Heavy Industries <7011.T>. [ID:nL5N0OT1S3] Hitachi Ltd <6501.T> said it hoped to join Mitsubishi and Siemens in their joint bid for Alstom's energy assets, which the Nikkei newspaper said would be worth 1 trillion yen ($9.80 billion). [ID:nL4N0OT1J0]  ** Spanish billionaire Esther Koplowitz could sell some of her stake in the holding company that controls builder FCC <FCC.MC> as part of a debt restructuring deal, said a source who is working on the refinancing. [ID:nL5N0OT202]  ** Swedish private equity firm IK Investment Partners said it had sold its stake in industrial fire fighting equipment maker Minimax Viking Group to Danish Kirkbi A/S and capital manager Intermediate Capital Group. [ID:nL5N0OT20J]  ** Orco Property Group <ORCO.PA> <ORCO.PR> has agreed to sell a 24.9 percent stake in Croatian hotels group Suncani Hvar, the central European developer said. [ID:nL5N0OT1SI]  ** Budget airline Citilink, owned by Garuda Indonesia <GIAA.JK>, has ended talks to acquire low-cost rival Tigerair Mandala, said two sources familiar with the discussions. [ID:nL4N0OT1TY]  ** Orange <ORAN.PA> Deputy Chief Executive Pierre Louette on Thursday said no deal term sheet or agreement existed with Bouygues <BOUY.PA> over the sale of France's third-largest mobile operator to its biggest player. [ID:nL5N0OT1WM]  ** Russia's Gazprom <GAZP.MM> has decided to sell its stakes in Lithuanian gas utility Lietuvos Dujos <LDJ1L.VL> and gas grid company Amber Grid <AMG1L.VL> to Lithuanian state-owned firms, a spokeswoman for Lithuania's prime minister said on Thursday. [ID:nL5N0OT1HO]  ** AstraZeneca <AZN.L> has struck a deal worth up to $232 million in milestone payments to acquire rights to a drug from Synairgen <SYNG.L> for treating respiratory tract viral infections in patients with severe asthma. [ID:nL5N0OT166]  ** The Pakistan government is set to raise $388 million after pricing the sale of its 19.8 percent stake in United Bank Ltd <UBL.KA> at 158 rupees per share, IFR reported. [ID:nL4N0OT0V4]  ** Leighton Holdings Ltd <LEI.AX>, Australia's largest construction firm, said it might sell its John Holland roads and rail business as Spanish-controlled majority owner Hochtief AG <HOTG.DE> seeks to cut debt and potentially finance a bid for full ownership. [ID:nL4N0OT020]  ** Plains Cotton Cooperative Association, one of the largest cotton merchants in the United States, has sold its denim mills that supply big-name brands like Wrangler, the latest in a recent wave of deals transforming the U.S. textile industry. [ID:nL2N0OS2BC]  ** Imperial Tobacco Group Plc <IMT.L> is evaluating a deal for assets likely to be divested from Reynolds American Inc <RAI.N> and Lorillard Inc <LO.N> if the two U.S. tobacco companies proceed with a proposed combination, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0OS25C]  ** Morocco's state-run phosphate monopoly OCP has signed an agreement to buy a 10 percent stake in Brazil-based company Fertilizantes Heringer <S.A> <FHER3.SA> for 145 million Brazilian real ($65 million), a statement from the Moroccan company said. [ID:nL5N0OS64K]  ** The union representing engineers at Spirit Aerosystems Holdings <SPR.N>, one of Boeing Co's <BA.N> biggest suppliers, said it had asked Spirit about the rumored sale of its fabrication business to GKN Aerospace, prompted by information supplied by its membership. [ID:nL2N0OS256]  ** Indonesia's government has dropped a plan for PT Bank Mandiri <BMRI.JK> to buy PT Bank Tabungan Negara <BBTN.JK>, the chief economic minister said. [ID:nL4N0OT2I7]  ** Italian cement maker Italcementi <ITAI.MI> said its takeover bid on its French unit Ciments Francais would start on June 13 and end on July 3. [ID:nI6N0OM04X]  ** Eni <ENI.MI> said it had signed an agreement with Kazakhstan state-owned KazMunayGas to jointly explore an offshore oil field that would allow the Italian oil major to grow its presence in Kazakhstan. [ID:nI6N0OM04Q]  ** Consol Energy Inc <CNX.N> and Noble Energy Inc <NBL.N> said they would form a master limited partnership for pipeline operations they control in Pennsylvania's Marcellus shale region. [ID:nL2N0OT0FY]